  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dad\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0dba \u0db6\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China hands over first batch of rice",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Chinese Embassy has officially handed over the first batch of 10,000 metric tons of rice from China to the Ministry of Education.",
        "The first batch consisted of 1000 metric tons of rice. Minister Bandula Gunawardena officially accepted the stock of rice.",
        "Chinese Ambassador to China Chi Chenhong said that the donation of 10,000 metric tons of rice will help support the school nutrition program to provide food to 7900 school children across Sri Lanka.",
        "Chinese Ambassador to Sri Lanka Chi Chenhong said that Sri Lanka will receive the second and third installments of the grant over the next two weeks and hopes to strengthen the school food program for at least six months."
      ],
